         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/3/95. ¶  ¶ Yesterday the weekly mail brought the new part of your Analecta, ¶ Agardh (1894-1903),Continuatio 2. ¶  ¶ noble Sir, a wonderful incomparable work of an octogenarian! It was pleasing to m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">95.03.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. Avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">7/3/95.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gestern brachte die Wochen-Post den neuen Theil Ihrer Analecta, edler Herr, ein wunderbares unvergleichliches Werk eines Octogenars! Es war mir lieb, gleich in Nachtstunden daraus zu ersehen dass sowohl Wilson's wie meine Sendungen so wichtiges Neues lieferten. Miss Hussey wird sich besonders über deren Erfolge freuen in Ihrer<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>ihrer.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Abgeschiedenheit als eine Taubstumme. Nach einem Photogram, welches ich von ihr erbat ist sie eine sehr schöne junge Dame mit geistreichem Ausdruck. Wenn Sie es wünschen, könnte ich diese unsere Helferin ersuchen, auch Ihnen ihr Bild zu senden. Könnten Sie mir noch ein Exemplar der beiden letzten Anaclecta<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>error for Analecta.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>zukommen lassen, so wäre es bei ihr gut angebracht</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Auch Capt Fairchild and Miss King werde ich von Ihren Angaben Mittheilung machen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wie schön wäre es, wenn wir einen einfachen Census der Algen ganz Australiens hätte, um Alles schnell übersehen zu können Mein Census der Vascular Pflanzen Australiens (9000 Arten sehr conservativ gehalten) erleichtert mir täglich meine Arbeiten.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Immer Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/3/95.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yesterday the weekly mail brought the new part of your Analecta,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Agardh (1894-1903),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Continuatio 2.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>noble Sir, a wonderful incomparable work of an octogenarian! It was pleasing to me, to ascertain from it right away in the night hours that both Wilson's and my consignments supplied such important new things. Miss Hussey will be particularly pleased about her success in her solitude as a deaf-mute.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was mistaken. Jessie Hussey went deaf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>after an illness in about 1888 ('The late Miss J. L. Hussey',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Adelaide observer</seg>, 25 March 1899, p. 46). She<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was not mute, for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>she presented<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>an illustrated talk 'A few notes on South Australian algae' to the Field Naturalists' Section of the Royal Society of South Australia in June 1897 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Advertiser</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Adelaide), 16 June 1897, p. 5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>According to a photograph that I requested from her,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Photograph held at Library, Royal Botanic Gardens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>she is a very pretty young lady with an intelligent expression. If you want I could ask<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>this our helper also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>send you her picture. If you could send me another copy of both the last Analecta,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Agardh (1894-1903),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Continuatio 1, Continuatio 2.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>they would be well placed with her.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>shall<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also inform Captain Fairchild and Miss King of your statements.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>How convenient it would be if we had a simple census of the algae of the whole of Australia, so as to be able quickly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have an overall view of everything. My census of vascular plants of Australia<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B89.12.03.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M had previously prepared a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Evasculares, including algae, using this model, but it was never published; see M to W. Mitten, 22 November 1881<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 81-11-22a), n. 4.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(9000 species very conservatively regarded) daily makes my work easier for me.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
